<font color="#FF0000">HONOR THE PROTESTORS</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec 14 15:56:31 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I stood up to screaming patriots, and burned my draft card.  I protested and marched, screamed and cried, told my generation to stop, don't go, this was was wrong.  I ended up a C.O. doing 2 years of bedpans, not smoking dope in canada.  I think that I, and those like me, are the true patriots, the true disenters, who tried to stop 50,000 of our generation from coming home in bags.  What did we achieve? NOTHING !  The Peace Movement was never that, it was just ,anti war, and when Nam ended, so did the movement.  No memorial wall, no etched names for the resistors, not even the God Damn GI Bill benefits, and I gave up 2 years of my life too.  When will America wake up and acknowledge that the protestors, SDS, and war resistors were right??  We don't need the McNamara confessions to validate us, but some serious acknowledgement of our being right would be nice.   Nam is a weight that I carry too.
